  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Network Engineer",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for Network Engineers who experienced in designing, implementing, and maintaining enterprise-level network infrastructure: </p><p><strong>Load Balancers (Core):</strong></p><ul><li>F5 BIG-IP: Advanced configuration and management<br /></li><li>Alternative products: Citrix ADC (NetScaler), NGINX Plus, HAProxy<br /></li><li>Experience in application delivery, SSL offloading, and traffic management<br /></li></ul><p><strong>Network Routing and Switching (Core):</strong></p><ul><li>Cisco: IOS, Nexus series configuration and troubleshooting<br /></li><li>Alternative products: Juniper Networks, Arista Networks, HPE (Aruba)<br /></li><li>Proficiency in OSPF, BGP, EIGRP, and VLANs<br /></li></ul><p><strong>Next-Generation Firewalls (Core):</strong></p><ul><li>Check Point: Configuration, policy management and threat prevention<br /></li><li>Palo Alto Networks: Configuration, policy management and threat prevention<br /></li><li>Alternative products: Fortinet FortiGate, Cisco Firepower<br /></li><li>Proficient in On-Premise firewall equipment and Cloud firewall instances<br /></li><li>Proficient in dynamic routing protocols<br /></li><li>Experience in implementing zero-trust network architectures<br /></li></ul><p><strong>Cloud Network Security (Core):</strong></p><ul><li>Azure Firewall: Design and implementation in Azure environments<br /></li><li>Alternative products: AWS Network Firewall, Google Cloud Armor<br /></li><li>Skilled in cloud-native network security best practices<br /></li></ul><p><strong>Application Gateways (Core):</strong></p><ul><li>Azure Application Gateway: Configuration and management<br /></li><li>Alternative products: AWS Application Load Balancer, Google Cloud Load Balancing<br /></li><li>Experience in web application firewall (WAF) implementation<br /></li></ul><p><strong>Intrusion Detection Prevention Systems (IDPS):</strong></p><ul><li>Implementation and management of IDPS solutions<br /></li><li>Experience with products like Check Point, Palo Alto Networks<br /></li><li>Alternative products: Fortinet, Cisco Firepower, Suricata<br /></li><li>Skilled in configuring, tuning, and maintaining IDPS rules and policies<br /></li><li>Proficient in analyzing IDPS logs and responding to security incidents</li></ul><p><br /><strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong></p><p>Bachelor’s degree in IT, Computer Science, or related field (or equivalent experience).</p><p>Minimum of 5 years of hands-on experience.</p><p>At least Cisco Certified Network Professional (CCNP)</p><p>Experience with deployment and support of Cisco SDWAN, Cisco ACI, F5 load balancers, Checkpoint or Palo Alto Firewalls</p><p>Experience with performing CIS hardening on network devices, perform security assessment and remediation.</p><p>Familiar with ITIL best practices and processes</p><p>Good knowledge of networking (IP addressing, routing, VLANs)</p>",
